<title>USA: GM idled workers drops from Tuesday.</title>
<headline>GM idled workers drops from Tuesday.</headline>
<dateline>WARREN, Mich. 1996-10-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>General Motors Corp said Wednesday it has idled 19,159 workers in the U.S. and Mexico as a result of the Canadian autoworkers strike, down 772 workers from the total Tuesday.</p>
<p>The change came from 803 workers who were sent back to work at GM's Delphi Automotive Systems plants, and 31 more workers who were idled at GM's Mansfield Metal fabricating plant in Ohio.</p>
<p>GM and the Canadian Auto Workers reached a tentative deal on a new contract Tuesday. GM said it cannot speculate on how many other facilities will be affected because it depends on how soon Canadian workers resume operations.</p>
<p>However, the company has said it told 2,000 workers at its Lordstown, Ohio, assembly plant to not show up for their shifts on Friday.</p>
<p>The 19,159 workers affected do not include the 26,000 CAW workes who were on strike.</p>
